description:
When epics roadmap is loaded, we load all epics data and milestone data in a single request which is quite expensive:

The GraphQL request we send:

```
[
  {
    "operationName": "groupEpics",
    "variables": {
      "labelName": [],
      "authorUsername": "",
      "search": "",
      "fullPath": "gitlab-org",
      "state": "opened",
      "sort": "start_date_asc",
      "startDate": "2020-4-26",
      "dueDate": "2020-8-8"
    },
    "query": "query groupEpics($fullPath: ID!, $state: EpicState, $sort: EpicSort, $startDate: Time, $dueDate: Time, $labelName: [String!] = [], $authorUsername: String = "", $search: String = "") {
  group(fullPath: $fullPath) {
    id
    name
    epics(state: $state, sort: $sort, startDate: $startDate, endDate: $dueDate, labelName: $labelName, authorUsername: $authorUsername, search: $search) {
      edges {
        node {
          ...BaseEpic
          parent {
            id
            __typename
          }
          __typename
        }
        __typename
      }
      __typename
    }
    __typename
  }
}

fragment BaseEpic on Epic {
  id
  iid
  title
  description
  state
  webUrl
  startDate
  dueDate
  hasChildren
  hasParent
  descendantWeightSum {
    closedIssues
    openedIssues
    __typename
  }
  descendantCounts {
    openedEpics
    closedEpics
    __typename
  }
  group {
    name
    fullName
    fullPath
    __typename
  }
  __typename
}
"
  },
  {
    "operationName": "groupMilestones",
    "variables": {
      "fullPath": "gitlab-org",
      "state": "active",
      "startDate": "2020-4-26",
      "dueDate": "2020-8-8",
      "includeDescendants": true
    },
    "query": "query groupMilestones($fullPath: ID!, $state: MilestoneStateEnum, $startDate: Time, $dueDate: Time, $includeDescendants: Boolean) {
  group(fullPath: $fullPath) {
    id
    name
    milestones(state: $state, startDate: $startDate, endDate: $dueDate, includeDescendants: $includeDescendants) {
      edges {
        node {
          id
          description
          title
          state
          dueDate
          startDate
          webPath
          projectMilestone
          groupMilestone
          subgroupMilestone
          __typename
        }
        __typename
      }
      __typename
    }
    __typename
  }
}
"
  }
]
```

For `gitlab-org`, it takes ~18s to process this request. 

### Proposal

Although most of the time takes processing of epics, we send two separate requests - one for milestones, one for epics, the benefit would be we would save about 1s which takes loading of milestones and it wouldn't take so long to show some roadmap data.
